<h id='crossBrowserSvg'><a href="https://w3future.com/weblog/2005/05/08.xml#a288" class="weblogItemTitle">Cross browser SVG</a></h>
<p><a href="ftp://ftp.mozilla.org/pub/mozilla.org/firefox/nightly/">Firefox 1.0+ builds</a> now have SVG enabled by default. To test it out I changed <a href="https://w3future.com/2005/svg/icosa/icosa.svg">an SVG animation</a> I created 2 years ago. It is a 3D animation of a cube morphing into an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Icosahedron">icosahedron</a>. It works in Firefox 1.0+ and in Internet Explorer with <a href="http://www.adobe.com/svg/viewer/install/beta.html">the Adobe SVG Plugin</a>. Sadly Opera 8, which has some SVG support, shows nothing at all.</p>
